cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper is about the ActivityNet Large-Scale Activity Recognition Challenge, which focuses on recognizing daily life activities from user-generated videos. The challenge involves tasks related to semantic visual understanding of videos, bridging visual content with human captions, and tracing evidence of activities in time. These tasks are related to computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
